===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# Agreement or [[concurrence]] of opinion, will, or action.
#* '''1769''', ''[[s:Bible_(King_James)|The King James Bible - Oxford Standard Text]]'', [[s:Bible_(King_James)/Acts#Chapter_1|Acts 1:14]]
#*: These all continued with one '''accord''' in prayer.
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|author=Francis Bacon|passage=a mediator of an '''accord''' and peace between them}}
# A [[harmony]] in sound, [[pitch]] and [[tone]]; [[concord]].
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=17th century|title=The Self-Subsistence of the Soul|author=[[w:John Davies (poet)|Sir John Davies]]|passage=Those sweet '''accords''' are even the angels' lays.}}
# Agreement or harmony of things in general.
#: {{ux|en|the '''accord''' of light and shade in painting}}
# {{lb|en|legal}} An agreement between parties in [[controversy]], by which satisfaction for an injury is [[stipulated]], and which, when [[executed]], prevents a lawsuit.
#: {{rfquotek|Blackstone}}
# {{lb|en|international law}} An international agreement.
#: {{ux|en|The Geneva '''Accord''' of 1954 ended the French-Indochinese War.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[assent|Assent]]
# Voluntary or spontaneous impulse to act.
#: {{ux|en|Nobody told me to do it. I did it of my own '''accord'''.}}
#* Bible, Leviticus xxv. 5
#*: That which groweth of its own '''accord''' of thy harvest thou shalt not reap.

