===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make to agree or [[correspond]]; to suit one thing to another; to [[adjust]].
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1590|author={{w|Philip Sidney}}|title={{w|The Countess of Pembroke's Arcadia}}|page=150|passage=[H]er hands '''accorded''' the Lutes musicke to the voice;}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To bring (people) to an agreement; to [[reconcile]], settle, adjust or [[harmonize]].
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|book=III|passage=But ''Satyrane'' forth stepping, did them stay / And with faire treatie pacifide their ire, / Then when they were '''accorded''' from the fray {{...}}}}
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|author={{w|Robert South}}|passage=all which particulars, being confessedly knotty and difficult, can never be '''accorded''' but by a competent stock of critical learning}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To agree or [[correspond]]; to be in harmony;  to be [[concordant#Adjective|concordant]].
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1593|author={{w|William Shakespeare}}|title=[[s:The Second Part of King Henry the Sixth|The Second Part of King Henry the Sixth]]|section=III-i|passage=For things are often spoke and seldom meant; / But that my heart '''accordeth''' with my tongue,—}}
#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Regained|book=3|page=54|lines=9–11|passage=Thy actions to thy words '''accord''', thy words / To thy large heart give utterance due, thy heart / Conteins of good, wiſe, juſt, the perfect ſhape.}}
#* {{RQ:EHough PrqsPrc|II|0147}}
#*: Carried somehow, somewhither, for some reason, on these surging floods, were these travelers,{{nb...}}. Even such a boat as the ''Mount Vernon'' offered a total deck space so cramped as to leave secrecy or privacy well out of the question, even had the motley and democratic assemblage of passengers been disposed to '''accord''' either.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To agree in pitch and tone.
# {{lb|en|transitive|legal}} To [[grant]] as suitable or proper; to [[concede]] or [[award]].
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1951|author=United Nations|title=[[s:1951 Refugee Convention|Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees]]|section=article 14|passage=In respect of the protection of industrial property,{{...}}a refugee shall be '''accorded''' in the country in which he has his habitual residence the same protection as is '''accorded''' to nationals of that country.}}
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|author=European Court of Human Rights|title=A, B and C v. Ireland|section=marginal 235|date=16-12-2010|issue=25579/05|url=http://hudoc.echr.coe.int/eng?i=001-102332|passage=In the present case, and contrary to the Government’s submission, the Court considers that there is indeed a consensus amongst a substantial majority of the Contracting States of the Council of Europe towards allowing abortion on broader grounds than '''accorded''' under Irish law.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|obsolete}} To give consent.
# {{lb|en|intransitive|archaic}} To arrive at an agreement.

